ADO-EKITI – Simon Ebegbulem, the Vanguard Correspondent in Edo State has been appointed the Chief Press Secretary to the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. Ebegbulem is a Senior Correspondent of Vanguard in Edo State and the South South. In a letter signed by the National Secretary of the APC, Hon.Mai. Mala Buni, it said Mr Ebegbulem shall “perform all the functions of a Chief Press Secretary and any such duties as may be assigned to you by the National Chairman”. Ebegbulem, a Jerusalem Pilgrimage (JP) and graduate of Mass Communication, has been in Vanguard for over fourteen years and has won several awards in journalism both in Nigeria and abroad. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 